                <supplied reason="lost">Α</supplied>ὐτοκράτορι <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost">Κ</supplied>αίσαρι <lb n="3"/><del rend="erasure">[<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></del>] <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">Ε</supplied>ὐσεβεῖ Εὐτυχε<supplied reason="lost">ι</supplied> <lb n="5"/>Σεβαστῶι <lb n="6"/><supplied reason="lost">ἐ</supplied>ξ ἄστεως <lb n="7"/>ϛ </ab></div><div n="2" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost">Σ</supplied>ε<supplied reason="lost">βα </supplied><lb break="no" n="3"/>στοῖς Βαλλ<supplied reason="lost">εν</supplied><lb break="no" n="4"/>τινιανῶ <lb n="5"/>καὶ Βαλέν<lb break="no" n="6"/>τι </ab></div><div n="3" type="textpart"><ab><lb n="1"/> <expan><abbr>Dd</abbr><ex>omini</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>n<am>n</am></abbr><ex>ostri</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/>Arcadiu<supplied reason="lost">s</supplied> <lb n="3"/><supplied reason="lost">e</supplied>t Honor<supplied reason="lost">ius</supplied> <lb n="4"/>sub <expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>iro</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>c</abbr><ex>larissimo</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/><supplied reason="lost">e</supplied>t specta<supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>b</abbr><ex>ili</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>proc</abbr><ex>onsule</ex></expan> <lb n="7"/>Eusebio <lb n="8"/>ς
            </ab></div></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Meilenstein mit zwei griechischen Inschriften und einer lateinischen. Drei weitere Erwähnungen des proconsuls Eusebius auf Meilensteinen: CIL III 573. 7308. 14203, 27. Entfernungsangabe in griechischen Zeichen. Am Ende der längeren griechischen Inschrift findet das attische Symbol für die Zahl 6 Verwendung. Material: hymettischer Marmor.</p>
            </div>
